The Acting General Officer Commanding (GOC) 7 Division, Brig. Gen. Abdulmalik Bulama Biu has promoted and decorated the Regimental Sergeant Major of the Division, Master Warrant Officer (MWO) Jurist Adam, with his new rank badge of Army Warrant Officer (AWO). The GOC who described the promotion as a reward for hard work, loyalty and dedication to service was speaking at the Headquarters of the Division in Maimalari Cantonment Maiduguri yesterday. A statement by the Director of Army Public Relations, Brig. Gen. Texas Chukwu said the GOC congratulated the new AWO for reaching the peak of his career, while urging him to impact the experience he gained over the years on younger generation. Jurist Adam was born to the family of Gaie Jurist of Ngwaafari, Jemaâ€™a Local Government Area of Kaduna State. He attended Ngwafari primary school and Kagoro Teachers College before his enlistement into the Nigerian Army on Jan 16, 1984 as a member of the 17th Regular Recruit intake.